results.title: Very Merry Christmas
results.description:
Hi there. Thank you for your order!

IMPORTANT: IF YOUR ORDER HAS MORE THAN ONE COLOR, EACH COLOR IS A SEPARATE LAYER AND YOU WILL NEED TO SEPARATE THEM PRIOR TO IRONING THEM ON. If you don't have a piece of parchment paper, a thin piece of material, like a pillowcase will work just as well.
ALSO, USE A FIRM AMOUNT OF PRESSURE WHEN IRONING THE LAYERS ON. HEAT PLUS PRESSURE WILL RESULT IN A PERFECT IRON-ON. Have fun! :)

Application instructions (home iron)

• Set iron dial between Cotton and Linen
• Cover design with Kraft paper or non-stick cover sheet
• Place on flat, hard surface (ironing board not recommended)
• Press iron with medium/firm pressure (do not slide iron)
• Press each section of design for 10-15 seconds
• If areas of design lift after application, replace cover sheet
and re-press for 5-10 seconds.

results.description:
Batik T-Shirt Vytis Lietuva 2XL Original Tee Historic Symbol Spiral Batik Cotton Shirt Unique Professional Tie Dye Tee Lithuanian Product

This is handmade unique batik shirt in one exemplar. T-shirt is decorated with symbol of Vytis, historical Coat of Arms of Lithuania, and motives of Sun. Ancient sign of Vytis is presented by reflection of unique archaeological find from 11th - 12th c. in Didvyciai, Lithuania. It is the oldest known interpretation of Vytis - historical Coat of Arms of Lithuanian State. 
The shirt is hand-dyed by professional artist of Batik technique. Produced of high quality cotton 100% with long-lasting printing. The process of dyeing covered three operations. High quality and sustainable dye was applied, color was fixed by special acid. Washable separately up to 40°C.

More options of batik t-shirts with historical symbols: https://www.etsy.com/shop/Baltvytis
